<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><div style="margin: 0px;"><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br></div><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">A very warm welcome back to Term 3. I hope that you all had a good celebration and a great time with your families. It is nice to be back and see all the staff and teachers refreshed and ready for the new exciting times ahead this term.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">I hope you have noticed the nice surprises we have created around the campus. We have yet again completed much work over the break to further improve the facilities for the BSY community which includes:</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">1. &nbsp; &nbsp; Shade and rain shelter at front of the school</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">2. &nbsp; &nbsp; Further work in the school theatre</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">3. &nbsp; &nbsp; Replacing tiles by the swimming pool waiting area and stairwell</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">4. &nbsp; &nbsp; Shade and shelter built between the main building and canteen</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">5. &nbsp; &nbsp; Louvre covers built around the top roof in the primary playground to prevent water coming through on to the floor</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">In the coming weeks we are also planning to complete the following works:</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">1. &nbsp; &nbsp; EYFS outside play area shade and shelter</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">2. &nbsp; &nbsp; Artificial grass sections on the primary playground for multi weather use</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">3. &nbsp; &nbsp; Increase water filter capacity on the swimming pool to assist with higher usage</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">So, whilst we have a nice new building there is still much for us to work on over time to ensure the building is the very best we can make it for our BSY community. Thank you for your continued patience as much of this work continues to take place.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Please be aware that we continue to monitor the air quality and temperatures hourly here at BSY. Whenever appropriate we will continue to cancel outdoor activities or events for the safety of your children.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">This week the school celebrated book week culminating in many staff and students dressing up as a book character today. There was a wonderful feel around the school and a lot of excitement about reading and books which is what we wish to promote at BSY. The day culminated in a book week character fashion parade on the field. It was great to see so many children and staff taking part in this wonderful celebration. A big thank you too all the staff who helped coordinate and run such a fun and exciting week of activities.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Tomorrow we are hosting the final inter school swimming gala at BSY. We wish all our competitors the very best of luck with the event. I would like to thank all the staff who have organised or have offered to support the event on Saturday in advance. It promises to be a great finale to the season of swimming.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Please be reminded that Wednesday 1st is a public holiday so the school will be closed all day.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">I wish you all a relaxing weekend.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Paul Holyome&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Principal&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br></span></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div></font></span></div><div style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" size="2">www.britishschoolyangon.org</font></p></div></div>]]></td>
